description: From Middle English different, from Old French different, from Latin differēns, present active participle of differō (“I differ”); see differ.

adjectives.description: different (comparative more different, superlative most different)

entries.meaning: Not the same; exhibiting a difference.
examples: One interesting feature was remarked by Dr. Peters, viz.: that the instrument used for the longitudes of the original catalogue was graduated differently to that used for the latitudes.

entries.meaning: Distinct, separate; used for emphasis after numbers and other determiners of quantity.
examples: Several different scientists all reached this conclusion at about the same time.

adverbs.description: different (comparative more different, superlative most different)
